    <fact xml:id="fact-washer">
        <title>The Washer Method</title>
        <statement>
      <p>
        If <m>y = R(x)</m> and <m>y = r(x)</m> are nonnegative continuous functions on <m>[a,b]</m> that satisfy
        <m>R(x) \ge r(x)</m> for all <m>x</m> in <m>[a,b]</m>,
        then the volume of the solid of revolution generated by revolving the region between them about the <m>x</m>-axis over this interval is given by
        <me>
          V = \int_a^b \pi [R(x)^2 - r(x)^2] \, dx
        </me>.
      </p>
            </statement>
    </fact>
    
    
    
