    <fact xml:id="fact-shell">
        <title>The Shell Method</title>
        <statement>
      <p>
        Let a solid be formed by revolving a region <m>R</m>, bounded by <m>x=a</m> and <m>x=b</m>, around a vertical axis. Let <m>r(x)</m> represent the distance from the axis of rotation to <m>x</m> (i.e., the radius of a sample shell) and let <m>h(x)</m> represent the height of the solid at <m>x</m> (i.e., the height of the shell). The volume of the solid is 
<me>V = 2\pi\int_a^b r(x)h(x)\ dx.</me>
      </p>
            </statement>
    </fact>
    
    
